			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As a side note, being a 65 BST that just got a copy of Sha's Advantage, the 50 slow, I can now often serve as primary slower for xp groups in PoV and it has greatly improved my ability to get a pick up group there.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
At first I thought the slow might not be good enough and cleric mana would be used up too fast on the MT but this has not proven to be the case, even mob stacking.  I tend to think the advantages to a melee class using slow helps mitigate the lower percentage.  By advantages I mean that we dont have to worry about a little initial agro so we can slow incoming mobs (instead of waiting for mobs health to be at 90% as some chanters do) and the fact that our high DPS will end the fight sooner.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
That said, where the improved slow would have been great at one time for soloing (in the old world) the only xp soloing I can do now is via agro kiting which is really not very efficient (compared to a PoV group) so I don't even bother using it for soloing.  I only have the 50 slow but I don't think the 65 slow will make any difference in my ability to stand toe to toe with hard hitting POV mobs.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Last note, every 65 BST I have talked to on my server (all of 3) seems to have Ferocity and none of them have Sha's Revenge.  Small data pool so we will see...I am BoT flagged and plan to take down some named soon   <i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
