				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My take on the slows. I found 30 percent slow sufficient in many groups in PoV and it was fun seeing people convinced. In a group mostly of 65's and high dps 30 percent is fine.
<br />

<br />
I now have Revenge and can definitely be primary slower with shaman or druid as main healer in PoS, PoV and BoT. Yes, last night we had the shaman heal and me slow in BoT.
<br />

<br />
However! We do not get malo or tash. This limits our usefulness as primary slower a little. Many mobs are resistent and I'm fortunate my wife is a mage and can provide not only nice dps but malo.
<br />

<br />
I find that Revenge definitely opens up group opportunities for me and most importantly it show-cases our class.<br />_________________<br /><p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=425102
<br />
>Rikard</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
