				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>nikatjef wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Greetings,
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>seamusmc wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">However! We do not get malo or tash. This limits our usefulness as primary slower a little.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
    Hmm, what mobs are you fighting?  I ask because I have had very little difficulty landing Lethargy on mobs.  I've even done various Velious raids where I could land it on mobs that were 15+ levels above me without malo.   Possibly Revenge is easier to resist?
<br />

<br />
   Anyway, I have followed this thread for some time now, and I always come back to the idea that was posted on the old site about scalaing our slows.  If our current slows are not sufficient, then simply scaling our slows as previously suggested would be the better way to go than what has been proposed here</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Certain Razorfiends and crystaline spiders in PoV resist all spells frequently without the help of tash or malo. Shaman and Enchanters have as tough a time with these as I do. Higher the level you are, the better chance you have to stick your spells. Frankly everyone hates having to do crystaline spiders because they can't be rooted, resist spells incredibly well and are hard as heck to see.
<br />

<br />
Some giants in PoS are also very resistent as well as some frogs. 
<br />

<br />
Some Bees, giants, and statue like creatures in BoT also have good resists. Bees are easier to slow then most.
<br />

<br />
You'll find the butterfly like creatures in PoN highly resistant to all spells.
<br />

<br />
Generally speaking you'll find the mobs in PoP zones much harder then many raid mobs in Pre-PoP zones. After PoV, NToV is a walk in the park. PoP has really dumbed down the old zones. Most level 65 mobs in the old zones don't hold a candle to the ones in PoP. I almost laughed the other day when one of Tunare's guards raged, as it was only hitting me in the 100's. Things in PoV hit for 500-700.<br />_________________<br /><p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=425102
<br />
>Rikard</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
